AGI - Today begins the fasting to relay launched by family members and supporters of&nbsp;Alberto Trentini, the 45-year-old Venetian co-operator arrested in Venezuela on 15 November during a humanitarian mission.&nbsp; You haven't heard from the man since he's been in jail. From today and throughout March it will be possible to fast in turn, for twenty-four hours. To take part in the fasting bracket just fill out the form on the site bit.ly/digiuno-alberto-trentini, indicating your data and the day you want to join.&nbsp; The initiative was launched on the Facebook page "Alberto Trentini libero". &nbsp;
The Italian government is silently at work but admits that there are difficulties. "We are continuing to work to try to bring him back to Italy, we are not renouncing any initiative, but I must say that it is not very easy", he recognized the vicepremier and foreign minister, Antonio Tajani. Yesterday on the case Trentini had said his also the Secretary of State to the Presidency of the Council, Alfredo Mantovano: "We are investing every effort to help them return, but to say more about the case would expose it to risks." &nbsp;
